==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Didymium
<hw>Di*dym"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
twin.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare metallic substance usually
associated with the metal cerium; -- hence its name. It was formerly
supposed to be an element, but has since been found to consist of two
simpler elementary substances, neodymium and praseodymium. See
<er>Neodymium</er>, and <er>Praseodymium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Didymous</ent>⟦br⟧
